      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {"data": []},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Since the data_processing_validator timed out, I'll try an alternative validation tool from the search results. I'll use the network_validator with a shorter timeout setting.

<tool_call>network_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {"data": []},
  "timeout": 10,
  "retry_count": 1,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll use the data_processing_transformer tool to transform the data we read earlier, using JSON as both input and output format for simplicity.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            I'll try the transformation again but specify XML as the input format since the error indicates it expects XML. I'll convert our JSON data to a simple XML structure for the transformation.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "xml",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "input_data": "<root><data></data></root>"
  }
}
</tool_call>

